  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Improving child safeguarding and care  at the school
- Teacher training and improving resources for the visually impaired
- Providing &apos;talking textbooks&apos; for children to learn independently</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Special Educational Needs Tigray (SENTigray) was officially established in September 2013.  They believe that, &#x2018;Every child deserves the right to receive a primary and secondary education.  It should be the inalienable right of every child to obtain an education to the maximum of his or her ability, despite any physical or mental handicap.&#x2019;
SENTigray is located in Mekelle, a town in the Tigray region of Ethiopia.  The organisation work with visually impaired children at the Mekelle Blind School (MBS).</narrative>
  </description>
